	source: ``,
	text: `Not only was WW2 the golden age of the battleship - and all the best known sailed those troubled times: Bismarck, Hood, Arizona, Yamato, and Missouri among many others - it also witnessed its demise. By the end warplanes, submarines, radar-guided missiles and other technological marvels had relegated battleships to floating shore batteries and rusting tourist attractions.`,
	tags: [],
