	source: ``,
	text: `We can only assume that as the human diet evolved, so did the underlying qualities of the gas they released. The gas produced after eating a lunch of berries and plant roots almost certainly differed from the gas built up from skinning and eating a wooly mammoth. The introduction of processed foods, pharmaceuticals, and Mexican restaurants has profoundly impacted the qualities of the modern fart.`,
	tags: [],
